The Bosch GDS 18V-400 Professional Cordless Impact Wrench is the most powerful tool in its class. It offers 400Nm of torque, ensuring that you can handle any job that comes your way. The tool has been designed specifically for use with metal, plastic and wood. The Bosch GDS 18V-400 Professional Cordless Impact Wrench has a powerful motor that drives the impact mechanism at 3,700 bpm. This allows you to remove and install bolts up to M20 in size quickly and easily. The ABR feature prevents overloading of the motor by stopping when the bolt is loose, so you do not have to keep pressing down on it while using it. The Bosch GDS 18V-400 Professional Cordless Impact Wrench is also extremely durable thanks to its high-quality materials and engineering. This means that it will last longer than other tools in its class without breaking down or losing performance capabilities over time. The GDS 18 V-400 is Bosch’s most powerful impact wrench in the mid torque class. It is ideal for use in various bolting applications, such as automotive repairs or industrial maintenance work. The device has a high breakaway torque of 600 Nm and a maximum impact rate of 3,700 bpm. This means that it can deal with even the toughest jobs quickly and efficiently. Its 400 Nm torque enables the user to tighten M 20 nuts (30 mm). If you are looking for an efficient tool that can handle all kinds of everyday bolt tightening tasks quickly and easily, then this powerful impact wrench is just right for you!

Lithium-ion cells and batteries meeting the requirements in this section are not subject to other additional requirements of these

Each cell and battery is of the type proven to meet the requirements of each test in the UN Manual of Tests and Criteria, Part III,
 subsection 38.3;

  • Cells and batteries must be manufactured under a quality management program;
  • For batteries, The Watt-hour rating must be marked on the outside of the battery case;
  • Each package must be capable of withstanding a 1.2m drop test in any orientation without:
  • Damage to cells or batteries contained therein;
  • Shifting of the contents so as to allow battery to battery (or cell to cell) contact;
  • Release of contents.

Each package must be labeled with a lithium battery handling label.
Section IB requirements apply to lithium-ion cells with a Watt-hour rating not exceeding 20 Wh and lithium-ion batteries with a Watthour rating not exceeding 100 Wh packed in quantities that exceed the allowance permitted in Section II, Table 965-II. Quantities of lithium-ion cells or batteries that exceed the allowance permitted in Section II, Table 965-II must be assigned to Class 9
and are subject to all of the applicable provisions of Regulation. Even classified as lithium batteries packed with equipment (UN3481), IATA Dangerous Goods Regulations packing instruction 966 is applied. Even classified as lithium batteries installed in equipment (UN3481), IATA Dangerous Goods Regulations packing instruction 967 is applied.
